reviews.review_text: Great Show - Greater Sugaree I have to say one of the finest Sugarees out there.  Twice as long as other 'rees that I like, but something was going well for them this evening.  I also like the Scarlet Fire.  Great job by the band, kudos to the restoration effort.

WOW This is one of the top 5 shows from 1978 without a doubt. Look at what we got here, a 17 minute "He's Gone", a 14 minute "Sugaree". I've noticed it's always a killer show the whole way through when the first set opens with a really long "Sugaree". Scarlet/Fire is great as well. Too many highlights in this show to write about. See for yourself. Sound is pretty good for an AUD as well!

Sweet Bean According to this site it was the last GD show in which Jerry played a Travis Bean guitar, and from the sound of things they are correct.

A nice show sadly to be missed by all board whores.

http://www.wald-electronics.com/TravisBeans.html
Wowwwww Jeeze man, this is amazing. LLR one of my favorites, so beautifully played. No qualms here.

rockin´ 78´ a very well played show with some really rockin moments and alot of fine jamming.gr8 first set with jerry starting strong on sugaree.set 2 is awesome nice scarlet.the other one is sweet.gr8 wharf rat.
